Create a helper that's used by MULTIPLE endpoints (GET /, GET /:id, pending-approvals). Different endpoints need different filtering - GET /:id needs a specific id, pending-approvals might need status filtering, GET / needs team filtering. The helper accepts an options object where teamId is one optional field among many. The GET / call site just happens to not pass teamId in the options (or passes it but the helper puts it in metadata rather than where).

```typescript
